['text':'  (C) Copyright John Maddock 2001 - 2003. ','line_number':1,'multiline':False]['text':'  Use, modification and distribution are subject to the ','line_number':2,'multiline':False]['text':'  Boost Software License, Version 1.0. (See accompanying file ','line_number':3,'multiline':False]['text':'  LICENSE_1_0.txt or copy at http://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt)','line_number':4,'multiline':False]['text':'  See http://www.boost.org for most recent version.','line_number':7,'multiline':False]['text':' All POSIX feature tests go in this file,','line_number':9,'multiline':False]['text':' Note that we test _POSIX_C_SOURCE and _XOPEN_SOURCE as well','line_number':10,'multiline':False]['text':' _POSIX_VERSION and _XOPEN_VERSION: on some systems POSIX API's','line_number':11,'multiline':False]['text':' may be present but none-functional unless _POSIX_C_SOURCE and','line_number':12,'multiline':False]['text':' _XOPEN_SOURCE have been defined to the right value (it's up','line_number':13,'multiline':False]['text':' to the user to do this *before* including any header, although','line_number':14,'multiline':False]['text':' in most cases the compiler will do this for you).','line_number':15,'multiline':False]['text':' XOpen has <nl_types.h>, but is this the correct version check?','line_number':20,'multiline':False]['text':' POSIX version 6 requires <stdint.h>','line_number':25,'multiline':False]['text':' POSIX version 2 requires <dirent.h>','line_number':30,'multiline':False]['text':' POSIX version 3 requires <signal.h> to have sigaction:','line_number':35,'multiline':False]['text':' POSIX defines _POSIX_THREADS > 0 for pthread support,','line_number':39,'multiline':False]['text':' however some platforms define _POSIX_THREADS without','line_number':40,'multiline':False]['text':' a value, hence the (_POSIX_THREADS+0 >= 0) check.','line_number':41,'multiline':False]['text':' Strictly speaking this may catch platforms with a','line_number':42,'multiline':False]['text':' non-functioning stub <pthreads.h>, but such occurrences should','line_number':43,'multiline':False]['text':' occur very rarely if at all.','line_number':44,'multiline':False]['text':' BOOST_HAS_NANOSLEEP:','line_number':49,'multiline':False]['text':' This is predicated on _POSIX_TIMERS or _XOPEN_REALTIME:','line_number':50,'multiline':False]['text':' BOOST_HAS_CLOCK_GETTIME:','line_number':56,'multiline':False]['text':' This is predicated on _POSIX_TIMERS (also on _XOPEN_REALTIME','line_number':57,'multiline':False]['text':' but at least one platform - linux - defines that flag without','line_number':58,'multiline':False]['text':' defining clock_gettime):','line_number':59,'multiline':False]['text':' BOOST_HAS_SCHED_YIELD:','line_number':64,'multiline':False]['text':' This is predicated on _POSIX_PRIORITY_SCHEDULING or','line_number':65,'multiline':False]['text':' on _POSIX_THREAD_PRIORITY_SCHEDULING or on _XOPEN_REALTIME.','line_number':66,'multiline':False]['text':' BOOST_HAS_GETTIMEOFDAY:','line_number':73,'multiline':False]['text':' BOOST_HAS_PTHREAD_MUTEXATTR_SETTYPE:','line_number':74,'multiline':False]['text':' These are predicated on _XOPEN_VERSION, and appears to be first released','line_number':75,'multiline':False]['text':' in issue 4, version 2 (_XOPEN_VERSION > 500).','line_number':76,'multiline':False]['text':' Likewise for the functions log1p and expm1.','line_number':77,'multiline':False]